Have you signed up for the 12 Days of Getting Lit freebies?

As you probably know, I have joined together with 13 other educators to gift you 14 structured literacy resources for FREE! We are sharing resources for K-3 students that would work with your whole class, small group, or one-one-one sessions. Check out our freebies!

@ogtutor - syllables
@daydreamingaboutdata - phonics prompts
@mwliteracy - long A patterns
@readlikearockstarteaching - silent e
@theliteracynest - syllable division VC/CV
@myliteracyspace - dictation practice templates
@leapingintolearning - CVC decodables
@droppinknowledgewithheidi - word mapping
@farmerlovesphonics - alphabet arcs
@readtorewire - welded sounds
@informedlit - decodable holiday readers
@snippetsbysarah - spin a sentence
@thedyslexiaclassroom - word chain
@theinstructionhub - silent e

SHARE this resource today!

The link to sign up is at the top of my profile. Drop the 🙌🏻 emoji and I’ll send you the direct link to sign up for all of these FREE structured literacy resources.
